node.text: Our first ever YouTuber awards show where we celebrate those in the YouTube fishing world for what they do best.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Karen: Did you know this is a private pond? The law requires that I answer "no"'.

node.text: Yep, had no idea I couldn't fish here... 😅

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'KARL'S POWER RANKINGS S”ast Fish: 1. ALL 2. FISH 3. ARE 4. SMART 49,634 BLUEGILL'.

node.text: I thought long and hard about this ranking, and I've come up with the perfect order 😎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3 PRESSURED WATER TIPS'.

node.text: It's awesome to see a ton of people out fishing! But it can make the bite tough. What tips do you use on pressured water?⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3 PRESSURED WATER TIPS'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'a STAND OUT Pressured water or high pressure from other anglers, is when there are lot of people fishing in one place. "I have seen this same jig 5 times today.. This means fish are seeing the same baits all day, and may stop biting them. Stand out by using baits no one else is using, or aren't as popular. Also, try mixing up your presentation.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2. EXPLORE Avoid the crowds and pressure by getting on the water early morning or fishing at night. Also, explore the area and go to hard to reach places other people won't go to, like the backs of creeks or small pockets. It doesn't have to be perfect, just has to be isolated.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3. DOWNSIZE In pressured water fish often avoid chunkier baits, and prefer smaller more finesse style baits. Slowing down or speeding up your retrieve can also help. Remember to try different retrieve speeds before changing lures or locations.'.
Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You smallmouth fishing Not catching footballs Your Fantasy Football team KARL'S Bait & Tackle THE CATCH'.

node.text: Tag someone this applies to...

node.text: I love reeling those buzzbaits as fast as I can 💯💯

node.text: What would be one tip you'd tell someone who just picked up a baitcaster for the first time?⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4 BAITCASTER TIPS FOR NEW ANGLERS 0v6'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '1. PRACTICE This is not a throw away tip, it's important! No one is born good at fishing with a baitcaster, it comes with practice and repetition. So don't let the fear of backlash or the frustration of starting, stop you from learning this sweet way to fish!'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2. HEAVY LINE When first starting out, use heavier line because it has a larger diameter and won't fly off the spoo as easily as lighter line will.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3. TENSION & BRAKES Adjust your nsio knob so when the bail opens, your lure free falls to the ground without backlashing. 8o And for beginners, try setting your braking system to the most brakes applied. Then slowly loosen the brake as you get more comfortable.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4. THUMB Remember to lightly leave your thumb on the spool while casting to help the spool avoid overrunning. And then increase thumb pressure again at the end of the cast!'.
Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 07, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Sometimes all a person needs is that one missing piece Double Digit Bass'.

node.text: Who's caught a double digit bass?
